  _shortDescription: Gunnery Support
  _longDescription: $HULLCOMP_AMMUNITION_ELEVATORS_DESC
  _flavorText: 'Usually semi-automated, someone still has to put the shells in their
    racks afterall. A good knock from a missile can shake the shells loose from their
    brackets and that''s just a disaster waiting to happen, just ask the Naval Office.


    Surprisingly,
    the 250mm brackets are just the right dimensions to hold 4 cases of Badnarik
    Draft. Until the Admiralty cracked down on it, crewmen would get clever and try
    to smuggle them around the gunnery crews.


    - T. Meadows, LT'
